## Pareto-frontier mode

The framework is tracking **multiple objectives** simultaneously and maintaining a Pareto frontier across them:

{% for obj in objectives %}
- **{{ obj.name }}** — {{ "maximize" if obj.direction == "max" else "minimize" }}
{% endfor %}

The profiler reports every objective as a numeric value in `metrics`. An offspring "wins" by being **non-dominated** — at-least-as-good as the parent on every axis and strictly better on at least one. A pure throughput gain that regresses latency may still be admitted (it adds a new frontier point), but a change that regresses *every* axis is wasted.

**Read the parent's per-axis numbers below** before deciding what to change. If the parent already wins one axis, don't double down on it — push the axis it loses on. The frontier expands fastest when offspring spread along axes the population is currently weak on.
{% endif %}

